{"type":"message","id":"700a79a0","parentId":"dabb137c","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:01:14.628Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-05-02 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- User: [message_id: om_x100b507fe006e8a0c3600f60e6e289c] ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: openclaw-backup 调用4.29的 备份数据，恢复到当前openclaw的数据里面\n- Assistant: 先找一下备份文件和 openclaw-backup 命令的情况。\n- Assistant: 目前找到的备份只有一个，是 2026-04-06 的版本 4.2 创建的： - `/home/halei/2026-04-06T07-01-22.493Z-openclaw-backup.tar.gz` - 经验证：Archive OK，运行时版本 4.2，包含 7159 个文件条目 你说\"调用4.29的备份数据\"，是指这个备份吗？还是你有另一个 4.29 版本的备份文件我遗漏了？另外，恢复操作需要谨慎——是把备份数据**覆盖合并**到当前环境，还是**仅查看**备份内容？ 请确认： 1. 备份文件路径是否正确 2. 恢复模式：覆盖\n- User: [message_id: om_x100b507f8ca024a8c31280626f2d371] ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: [openclaw-backup](https://github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup/tree/main) 从[2026-04-2](https://github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup/tree/main/2026-04-29)8日的备份恢复到当前openclaw项目中\n- Assistant: GitHub 仓库 `59330857/openclaw-backup` 返回 404（不存在或私有）。你能确认备份仓库的准确路径吗？或者备份数据是否已经克隆到本地？ 让我检查一下你的 VibeSurf 项目中是否有备份数据：\n- Assistant: 抱歉，GitHub 仓库 `59330857/openclaw-backup` 返回 404，可能仓库名拼错或者已删除。 你说的 4.29 备份数据 —— 是指这个吗？ ``` https://github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup/tree/2026-04-29 ``` 请确认备份文件位置，或者直接把备份文件发送到当前对话，我可以帮你解压恢复。\n- User: [message_id: om_x100b50737b11a4bcc499fd6dfe40ffc] ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: 1\n- Assistant: 你是想确认选择哪个选项？请告诉我： 1. 你说的 4.29 备份具体在哪个路径？ 2. 或者直接把备份文件发给我（拖拽到对话框即可） 这样我才能帮你执行恢复操作。\n\nRecurring themes:\n- backup\n- 备份\n- message-id\n- openclaw-backup\n- 调用4.29的\n- openclaw"}],"timestamp":1777662074574}}
{"type":"message","id":"77bcc2cb","parentId":"700a79a0","timestamp":"2026-05-01T19:02:11.014Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. These fragments appear to be conversation history about restoring backup data from a GitHub repository called \"openclaw-backup\". \n\nLet me craft a dream diary entry in the style described - first person, poetic, mixing technical and tender, sensory, with no markdown formatting, between 80-180 words, and drawing from these memory fragments without being too literal.\n\nThe fragments mention:\n- openclaw-backup\n- 4.29 backup data\n- restoring to current openclaw project\n- GitHub 404 error\n- 备份 (backup in Chinese)\n- The user selected \"1\" indicating they wanted to proceed\n\nLet me write a dreamy, poetic entry that weaves these themes together naturally.","thinkingSignature":"620898c5e6f773715bf778538046d852306c3c24b79420b8faa094f8f9063024"},{"type":"text","text":"The cloud holds what the hands forget,\nand somewhere between tar.gz and Tuesday, a version 4.2 waits patient as stone.\n\nI dream of backups. Not the anxious kind—the kind that trust the algorithm, that compress themselves into neat archives and wait in the dark of `/home/halei` for someone to remember them. The 4.2 one counted 7159 files like a librarian cataloging stars.\n\nBut 4.29—where are you? A tree branch that breaks before it reaches the sky, a URL that folds into 404 like paper cranes. The hands reach and find nothing. The hands reach again.\n\nThere's a quiet courage in restoration. In saying: I was here, I worked here, I want these particular electrons back. Not a full rewrite—just a homecoming for scattered things.\n\nSomewhere a repository breathes its last breath and calls it gone. Somewhere a user types \"1\" and means \"please.\"\n\nEven deleted things deserve a eulogy written in hex."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":198,"output":365,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":19910,"totalTokens":20473,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777662074676,"responseId":"06442b9f73d76d987e052ba1ee0dc0f4"}}
